<<EW_rebound>>=
kIs_light <- k * I_E_f * s_light
Re_EW_light <- Re_EW_func(kIs = kIs_light, Re_dev = Re_dev_light)
kIp_light <- k * I_E_f * p_E_f_light
dReEW_dRedev_light <- 1 - kIp_light
@ 

The economy-wide rebound for the case study can be calculated by Eq.~\ref{eq:Re_EW}, 
beginning with the value of $k I_{E_f} s$:
%
\begin{equation} \label{eq:kIs_light}
  k I_{E_f} s_{light} = \Sexpr{format(k, digits = 4)} 
                  \times \Sexpr{format(I_E_f, digits = 4)} \frac{\mathrm{\kWhr}}{\$} 
                  \times \Sexpr{format(s_light, digits = 4, nsmall = 4)} \frac{\$}{\mathrm{\kWhr}}
                  = \Sexpr{format(kIs_light, digits = 4)} \; ,
\end{equation}
%
followed by calculation of $Re_{EW,light}$:
%
\begin{equation} \label{eq:Re_EW_light}
  Re_{EW,light} = 1 - (1 - k I_{E_f} s) (1 - Re_{dev}) 
          = 1 - (1 - \Sexpr{format(kIs_light, digits = 4)})(1 - \Sexpr{format(Re_dev_light, digits = 4)})
          = \Sexpr{format(Re_EW_light, digits = 4)} \; .
\end{equation}

Finally, the first derivative of economy-wide rebound with respect to device-level rebound 
can be calculated using Eq.~\ref{eq:dRe_EW/dRe_dev}:
%
\begin{equation} \label{eq:dRe_EW/dRe_dev_val_light}
  \frac{\mathrm{d} Re_{EW,light}}{\mathrm{d} Re_{dev}} = 1 - k I_{E_f} p_{E_f}
                                                  = 1 - \Sexpr{format(kIp_light, digits = 5)}
                                                  = \Sexpr{format(dReEW_dRedev_light, digits = 4)} \; .
\end{equation}
%


